CI, integrations, and more.

66
00:02:44.505 --> 00:02:46.350
Let's compare the main aspects

67
00:02:46.350 --> 00:02:48.665
between OpenShift
and Kubernetes.

68
00:02:48.665 --> 00:02:49.970
OpenShift is a product,

69
00:02:49.970 --> 00:02:52.670
while Kubernetes is an
open source project.

70
00:02:52.670 --> 00:02:54.710
Installation on OpenShift has

71
00:02:54.710 --> 00:02:57.470
limited options after
the installation starts,

72
00:02:57.470 --> 00:02:59.370
while Kubernetes is installable

73
00:02:59.370 --> 00:03:01.230
on every Linux environment.

74
00:03:01.230 --> 00:03:03.070
OpenShift is less flexible,

75
00:03:03.070 --> 00:03:05.270
while Kubernetes
is more flexible.

76
00:03:05.270 --> 00:03:08.750
OpenShift is available online
with Azure and dedicated,

77
00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:11.450
while Kubernetes is
available on EKS,

78
00:03:11.450 --> 00:03:14.930
on AWS, GKE, on GCP,

79
00:03:14.930 --> 00:03:17.070
and AKS on Azure.

80
00:03:17.070 --> 00:03:19.590
OpenShift image streams
provide better management,

81
00:03:19.590 --> 00:03:20.990
while Kubernetes container

82
00:03:20.990 --> 00:03:23.140
image management
is not that easy.

83
00:03:23.140 --> 00:03:26.010
OpenShift has a very
strict security policy,

84
00:03:26.010 --> 00:03:28.605
while Kubernetes security
maintenance is easy.

85
00:03:28.605 --> 00:03:31.830
OpenShift router objects
permit external access,

86
00:03:31.830 --> 00:03:33.870
while Kubernetes ingress objects

87
00:03:33.870 --> 00:03:36.830
permit external access
to Kubernetes clusters.

88
00:03:36.830 --> 00:03:38.590
OpenShift uses the less

89
00:03:38.590 --> 00:03:40.710
flexible deployment
config command,

90
00:03:40.710 --> 00:03:44.110
while Kubernetes uses more
flexible deployment objects.

91
00:03:44.110 --> 00:03:46.450
OpenShift provides a
good user experience,

92
00:03:46.450 --> 00:03:48.750
while Kubernetes
requires extra tools

93
00:03:48.750 --> 00:03:50.625
for a better user experience.

94
00:03:50.625 --> 00:03:52.880
OpenShift provides
good networking

95
00:03:52.880 --> 00:03:54.220
solutions out of the box,

96
00:03:54.220 --> 00:03:56.840
while Kubernetes provides
third party plugins

97
00:03:56.840 --> 00:03:58.880
when network solutions
are unavailable.

98
00:03:58.880 --> 00:04:01.520
OpenShift provides a
good service catalog,

99
00:04:01.520 --> 00:04:03.640
while Kubernetes
offers less provision

100
00:04:03.640 --> 00:04:05.780
for better services in clusters.

101
00:04:05.780 --> 00:04:08.840
OpenShift has a user
friendly web console layout

102
00:04:08.840 --> 00:04:10.885
that is easy to
learn for beginners,

103
00:04:10.885 --> 00:04:12.780
while Kubernetes console layout

104
00:04:12.780 --> 00:04:14.905
is difficult to
learn for beginners.

